{
  "schema": 1,
  "comment": "The toolkit's shipped artifact set. tools/refresh.py reconciles a governed repo to exactly this set; installed governance is toolkit-owned (owner ruling 2026-07-16), so divergence is always drift and every run converges the repo. Classes: replace-whole (AGENTS.md: current or formerly-shipped versions update normally; divergent content is restored to current when git history shows a committed version once matched a shipped hash, and flagged as a foreign governance file - bootstrap, not refresh - when none ever did); replace (missing = install; matches a formerly-shipped version = update to current; anything else = drift, reported with its introducing commits and restored to current); retired (formerly-shipped target paths removed; drifted content is removed with a report - git history preserves it, and the dirty-tree refusal keeps uncommitted content from being machine-destroyed). All matching is newline-equivalent sha256: CRLF -> LF, and content differing only by at most one trailing final newline matches (issue #1). formerly[] lists normalized hashes of every version ever shipped, from git history. MAINTENANCE RULE: whenever a shipped source file changes, append the OUTGOING version's normalized hash to its formerly[] in the same commit - otherwise deployed copies of that version get reported as drift and restored instead of cleanly updated.",
